==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Entracte
<hw>En`tr'acte"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. Cf.
<er>Interact</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The interval of time which
occurs between the performance of any two acts of a drama.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A dance, piece of music, or interlude, performed
between two acts of a drama.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Entrail</ent>⟦br⟧
